11. Local and central inventory diffrences ?

=> 🔹 Local Inventory - IT IS INSIDE THE Oracle Home.
	
	👉 LOCATION --- $ORACLE_HOME/inventory
	👉 IT STORE Oracle Home information
	👉 Installed components
	👉 Patch history

	🔹 Example - 

	if server has 2 ORACLE_HOME, then will have to 2 local inventory hoga.

	🔹 Central Inventory - system level inventory

	👉 LOCATION --- /u01/app/oraInventory
	👉 IT STORE -- all Oracle Homes which installed on the servers
	👉 Oracle products list
	👉 Oracle Home locations
	👉 It stores entire software record Oracle server.


12. /************************* HIGH LEVEL STEPS OF PATCHING :: ****************************/

=> Prechecks -> Patching -> Postcheck

## Prechecks ::
--------------
i. Check the Backup status. Backup should be up to date. Take a backup with pfile as well. 
														**(LIST BACKUP;)**			
ii. Check invalid objects. **(v$db_objects / dba_objects)
iii. No LRT's (long running transactions). **(v$longops)
iv. Stop the Linstner. **(lsnrctl stop Linstner)
v. Stop database. **(srvctl stop database -d db_name)
vi. Download OPatch, unzip, analyze. Before stop DB, we've to opatch & patch S/W in our database.
vii. Check file system space. **(/mount point should have 13+ GB space). (df -h)
viii. Check last patch details. (opatch lsinventory)


## Postcheck ::
-----------------
i. Check patch has applied or not using './opatch lsinventory' command.
ii. Start database.
iii. Start Listner.
iv. Run utlrp.sql to check invalid object and revalidate it.
V. ./datapatch verbose (it register updated patch on data dictionary).
vi. Also, we have to check from sql> prompt that patch successfully applied or not. 
Using this view - 'dba_registry_sqlpatch';


## Patching ::
-------------------
Only we do - Apply patch. (./opatch apply).
	Once patch will be completed we do validate the patch using './opatch lsinventory'.
	Using this comman we got - i). last patch apply ii). list of patch iii). Give you log file location
	iv). home location  v). Inventory location  vi). date of time of when patch has applied.

