13. How to rollback of patch ?

=> 	🔹 Step 1

	👉 First we need to identify which patch are using.
	👉 To check go to -> Oracle Home -> opatch lsinventory
	👉 Using this we get to know - Patch number, Patch type and Oracle Home location.

	🔹 Step 2

	👉 'OPatch utility' is the main tool to Rollback.

	🔹 Rollback Steps (Database Patch)

	👉 Step 1: Database shutdown - SQL> SHUTDOWN IMMEDIATE;
	👉 Step 2: Listener stop - lsnrctl stop
	👉 Step 3: Go to Oracle Home - cd $ORACLE_HOME/OPatch
	👉 Step 4: Rollback command - opatch rollback -id PATCH_NUMBER 
						Example  - (opatch rollback -id 34765931)
	👉 Step 5: Start listener & database - lsnrctl start & STARTUP;
======================================================================================

14. what is the purpose of datapatch verbose ?

=> Command: $ORACLE_HOME/OPatch/datapatch -verbose

  🔹 PURPOSE --

	👉 It update the dictionary objects of Database.
	👉 Execute SQL scripts of Patch. 
	👉 Synchronize Database aur Oracle Home.
	👉 Show the Detailed output of patch.

  🔹 Agar datapatch run na kare toh kya hoga --

  	👉 Patch will be incomplete.
